        "content": "Maester Tomas remained in his study, unaware of the apprentice's progress at the archives. He sat surrounded by stacks of books, pulling volume after volume from the shelves with increasing agitation.\n\n*Chronicles of the Veyrosi Peace.* He flipped through it, scanning for primary source citations. References to the treaty, yes. Descriptions of its terms. But the actual document? \"See Royal Archives, restricted collection,\" the footnote read.\n\n\"Restricted,\" Tomas muttered darkly. \"How convenient.\"\n\nHe pulled down another tome\u2014*The Reign of Aldric II: A Complete Accounting*. More references. More secondhand descriptions. He began making notes, his handwriting growing increasingly cramped and hurried:\n\n*\"Treaty mentioned in 14 sources examined thus far. NONE cite direct viewing of signed document. All reference 'archives' or 'royal records' without specifics. Circular sourcing?\"*\n\nThe realization settled over him like a cold draft. He had built his understanding on what other scholars had written, who had themselves relied on earlier scholars, who had perhaps relied on... what? Court announcements? Official proclamations? \n\nHe stood abruptly, knocking over an inkwell. Black liquid spread across his notes, and he cursed, dabbing at it ineffectually with his sleeve.\n\n\"Forty-four years,\" he said aloud, staring at the ruined page. \"If the political state of war lasted until 891, then Queen Mira didn't dissolve the Conclave as a reformist gesture. She ended an active conflict.\" \n\nThe implications cascaded through his mind, rewriting decades of accepted interpretation. He began pacing again, speaking to the empty room as if lecturing.\n\n\"Which means the Conclave purges of 870 weren't persecution of a defeated enemy\u2014they were military actions against an active belligerent. Which means the Mage Rebellions of the 880s weren't rebellions at all, but continuations of...\" He stopped, pressing his palms against his temples.\n\n\"Gods above and below, we've had the entire framework wrong.\"\n\nHe looked toward the door where the apprentice had departed, then at the growing pile of books on his desk. For the first time in years, Maester Tomas felt something he'd almost forgotten\u2014the sharp, uncomfortable thrill of not knowing the answer.\n\nIt terrified him.\n\nIt also, though he would never admit it aloud, excited him more than anything had in a very long time.\n\nHe sat back down and began writing furiously, starting a new document: *\"A Reexamination of the Treaty of Veyros: Preliminary Notes on the Declassified Evidence.\"*\n\nIf his life's work was to be overturned, he would be damned if he wasn't the one doing the overturning."
