        "content": "Maester Tomas let out a sound somewhere between a harrumph and a sigh\u2014a signal, to those who knew him, of reluctant approval. \u201cDo not thank me, apprentice. Your gratitude is misplaced; truth is its own taskmaster, and she is never satisfied.\u201d He watched the apprentice\u2019s uncertain hands shuffle the cards, noting the tension in those young fingers with a faint, concealed trace of amusement.\n\nHe returned his attention to the manuscript before him, but did not dip his stylus. \u201cCuriosity is a double-edged tool,\u201d he said, voice softer now, almost reflective. \u201cLeft unchecked, it leads to folly and wild conjecture. Disciplined, it becomes the engine of learning.\u201d He paused, as if measuring the weight of his next words. \u201cIf you find something in those archives\u2014something that endures close examination, that forces us to reconsider what we know\u2014bring it to me. Not before.\u201d\n\nHe looked up, meeting the apprentice\u2019s gaze with unexpected candor. \u201cA maester\u2019s humility is not in refusing to question, but in admitting when the evidence compels us to answer anew. But until that day, we honor what is best supported, not what is most exciting.\u201d\n\nHe lifted a hand, dismissing further debate. \u201cNow, enough idle chatter. The scrolls of Northmarch are a shambles, and if you misplace so much as a single slip, I shall set you to copying the Lexicon of Lost Years\u2014*by hand*\u2014until your fingers are as stained as my own.\u201d The threat was ritual, but not without affection."
